translated: Björkman, Maths Arne was a assistant priest from Älem. He was born on July 29, 1910 in Kalmar to parents Maths B. and AmeHe Karlson, who were farmers. He married Ella Månsson in 1940 and had four children: Lena (born 1941), Karin (born 1942), Gunilla (born 1945), and Inger (born 1946). He passed his studentexamen (equivalent to high school diploma) in Kalmar in 1928, obtained a Bachelor's degree in Arts in Lund in 1932, a Bachelor's degree in Theology, passed his practical theology exam, and was ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1937. He served as an assistant priest in Botosö, temporary and curate assistant priest in Färgaryd, pastor in Hemmesjö, pastorsadjunkt (assistant pastor) in Norrahammar, and army chaplain in the Småland regiment. He became an assistant priest in Älem in 1943. He was also a substitute teacher for Hyltebruk's municipality's middle schools in two periods.
